content:
Create Another Salesforce Local Data Connection

From Data Manager, click the Connections tab. Click New Connection. Click Salesforce Connector and Next. Enter the connection settings:

Connection Name: Identifies the connections. Use a convention that lets you easily distinguish between different connections.
Developer Name: API name for the connection. This name can’t include spaces.
Description: Description for the connection, used to remind you why you added the connection or what it’s used for.

After entering the settings, save your changes. With the local connection created, you can add new objects to sync, move existing objects from another local connection, or filter which data is synced.

When using data from multiple local connections in a recipe, event-based scheduling will run only after all local connections are synced.
title: Creating Salesforce Local Data Connections
